# code-executor
🚀 Code-Executor – Run Multiple Languages in VS Code!
Code-Executor is a powerful and lightweight VS Code extension that allows you to run code in multiple programming languages directly from your editor. No need to switch terminals – just write your code and execute it instantly! ⚡

🌟 Features
✅ Supports Multiple Languages – JavaScript, Python, C++, Java, PHP
✅ Execute Code Instantly – No external setup required
✅ Seamless Integration – Works within the VS Code environment
✅ Lightweight & Fast – Optimized for performance

📥 Installation
Open VS Code
Go to Extensions Marketplace
Search for: Code-Executor
Click Install ✅
OR Install Manually
git clone https://github.com/your-repo/code-executor.git
cd code-executor
npm install
code --extensionDevelopmentPath=.
🚀 How to Use
Open any JavaScript, Python, C++, Java, or PHP file
Press Ctrl+Shift+P and select "Run Code with Code-Executor"
View the output directly in VS Code!
🛠️ Supported Languages
🔹 JavaScript → Executes using Node.js
🔹 Python → Runs via Python interpreter
🔹 C++ → Compiles with GCC
🔹 Java → Uses Java compiler & runtime
🔹 PHP → Runs through PHP interpreter

💡 Why Use Code-Executor?
🚀 Fast & Efficient – Execute your code without leaving VS Code
🔄 Multi-Language Support – No need for multiple setups
🛠️ Beginner-Friendly – Simple commands to get started

